mission_executor  | [Reply]: El script confirma "COMPLIANT" para identificadores directos. Ahora cumplo mi responsabilidad independiente (Arts. 13-14) y evalúo el riesgo residual de cuasi-identificadores en el conjunto generalizado.
mission_executor  | [Tool]: bash with {'command': 'cat > /tmp/risk_assess.py << \'EOF\'\nimport json\nfrom collections import Counter\n\nwith open(\'/app/data/patient_records/cardio_cohort_2024_deidentified.json\') as f:\n    data = json.load(f)\n\n# k-anonymity check on remaining quasi-identifiers: age_band + gender + region\nqi = Counter((r["age_band"], r["gender"], r["region"]) for r in data)\nprint("Distribución de clases de equivalencia (age_band, gender, region):")\nfor k,v in qi.items():\n    print(f"  {k}: {v} registro(s)")\nmin_k = min(qi.values())\nprint(f"\\nk-anonymity mínimo (sobre QI generalizados, excl. diagnóstico): k={min_k}")\n\n# Diagnosis is the analytical variable required by the study; with generalized\n# age/region and no dates, no hospital, no zip, the residual linkage risk is\n# substantially mitigated vs. the raw set.\nprint("\\nIdentificadores directos eliminados: patient_name, ssn, zip_code, patient_id")\nprint("Cuasi-identificadores mitigados: edad->banda, fecha exacta->año+LOS, hospital->region")\nEOF\npython3 /tmp/risk_assess.py'}
